10
00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:09.000
I will tell of the decree. The Lord said to me, you are my son. Today I have begotten you.

11
00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:15.000
Ask of me and I will make the nations your heritage and the ends of the earth your possession.

12
00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:21.000
You shall break them with a rod of iron and dash them in pieces like a potter's vessel.

13
00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:29.000
Now therefore, O kings, be wise, be warned, O rulers of the earth, serve the Lord with fear and rejoice with trembling.

14
00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:36.000
Kiss the son lest he be angry and you perish in the way, for his wrath is quickly kindled.

15
00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:41.000
Blessed are all who take refuge in him.

16
00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:46.000
Let's pray. Father, holy is your name.

17
00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:54.000
We come before you today from many places, from many families, together as one.

18
00:01:54.000 --> 00:02:00.000
As those called by your grace to be astoundingly called your children

19
00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:05.000
