219
00:19:38.000 --> 00:19:41.000
It sounds like for really important people, right?

220
00:19:41.000 --> 00:19:48.000
So they need to be wise and sure, make sure that they are warned about their authority.

221
00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:54.000
But I would implore you and myself to maybe recognize, especially where we find ourselves,

222
00:19:54.000 --> 00:19:59.000
we do carry and bear responsibility and authority to a point.

223
00:19:59.000 --> 00:20:05.000
Many of us have wealth unimaginable to the people that this was originally written to and among.

224
00:20:05.000 --> 00:20:10.000
Wealth unimaginable and authority unimaginable to people across the globe.

225
00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:16.000
The idea of being able to get in your own automobile and dictate your schedule for the day

226
00:20:16.000 --> 00:20:21.000
is something that most of humans across history would not even have a concept for.

227
00:20:21.000 --> 00:20:27.000
So maybe recognize that we do have authority and with that,

228
00:20:27.000 --> 00:20:33.000
I ought to quote Spider-Man with that responsibility, with great power comes great responsibility.

229
00:20:33.000 --> 00:20:36.000
So be wise and be warned.

230
00:20:36.000 --> 00:20:39.000
Verse 11, serve the Lord with fear.

231
00:20:39.000 --> 00:20:42.000
Serve the Lord with fear.

232
00:20:42.000 --> 00:20:46.000
So we see in Proverbs, many of us have maybe heard it quoted,

233
00:20:46.000 --> 00:20:49.000
that the fear of the Lord is the beginning of wisdom.

234
00:20:49.000 --> 00:20:53.000
There's something earlier we mentioned about disordered fears.

235
00:20:53.000 --> 00:20:57.000
It is not that there is no fear in life, right?

236
00:20:57.000 --> 00:20:59.000
There are things that it's good to be afraid of.

237
00:20:59.000 --> 00:21:03.000
It's good to teach your child to be afraid of the hot stove.

238
00:21:03.000 --> 00:21:11.000
It's difficult sometimes to teach some children that maybe don't climb up that high.

239
00:21:11.000 --> 00:21:15.000
You need to be afraid of that height because you could fall.

240
00:21:15.000 --> 00:21:21.000
But properly ordered fears are good.

241
00:21:21.000 --> 00:21:27.000
So maybe serving with fear is the proper posture that we come with.

242
00:21:27.000 --> 00:21:31.000
But then immediately after that, rejoice with trembling.

243
00:21:31.000 --> 00:21:38.000
This would be a rejoicing that's characterized by joy, exhilaration.

244
00:21:38.000 --> 00:21:40.000
Think about the things that make you tremble.

245
00:21:40.000 --> 00:21:44.000
I tremble a little bit getting up here. I was anxious, a little nervous, but excited.

246
00:21:44.000 --> 00:21:49.000
Also a sense of awe would accompany this rejoicing.

247
00:21:49.000 --> 00:21:57.000
I'm going to do this too. I quoted Tolkien and I can't do that without a reference to Lewis.

248
00:21:57.000 --> 00:22:08.000
One of my favorite pictures of this rejoicing with trembling is when anyone in the Chronicles of Narnia stories encounters the king.

249
00:22:08.000 --> 00:22:18.000
Who is, again for those of you who may have forgotten your children's stories, a gigantic lion as long as you can.

250
00:22:18.000 --> 00:22:25.000
And there's a lion when one of the little girls, I think it's Lucy, hears that he's a lion.

251
00:22:25.000 --> 00:22:32.000
People have been talking about this king and she said, oh, he's a lion? Is he safe?

252
00:22:32.000 --> 00:22:36.000
And they look at her and they laugh and they say, of course he's not.

253
00:22:36.000 --> 00:22:42.000
Who said anything about safe? But he's good. He's the king.

254
00:22:42.000 --> 00:22:51.000
And then when they encounter him, it is almost a sense of trembling and also you're drawn to him, right?

255
00:22:51.000 --> 00:23:01.000
And so in that sense of trembling there is rejoicing because all of these things that we may be tempted to give our joy to,

256
00:23:01.000 --> 00:23:06.000
to give our attention to, they all come up short. They all seem to be done in vain.

257
00:23:06.000 --> 00:23:12.000
But there's one that isn't. There's one that actually far exceeds our expectations.

258
00:23:12.000 --> 00:23:22.000
And that one leaves us trembling, satisfied, and yet we know that there will never be too much desire in us for him.

259
00:23:22.000 --> 00:23:30.000
And so this is, this is what we're told is how we move forward.

260
00:23:31.000 --> 00:23:40.000
And then verse 12. So I said the rod of iron was probably the toughest one, but this might actually be the toughest one in terms of just disarming us, right?

261
00:23:40.000 --> 00:23:55.000
Kiss the sun. Kiss the sun. Embrace. I think this would be an intimate embrace to the king, which is exploding a lot of categories here, right?

262
00:23:55.000 --> 00:24:05.000
There's no decorum. We're kissing the sun. And this is actually where we see that I was asking the wrong question.

263
00:24:05.000 --> 00:24:13.000
How is not the question. We don't need a how so much as we need a who.

264
00:24:13.000 --> 00:24:21.000
So this is, this is the point of the passage. We've reached it. It's not a how.

265
00:24:21.000 --> 00:24:25.000
We do have all of these things happening and we're going to talk about those.

266
00:24:25.000 --> 00:24:35.000
But what we need is not a system, not, not a revamped 2.0 system to follow.

267
00:24:35.000 --> 00:24:42.000
Because no matter what system we put into place, we have broken sinful hearts.

268
00:24:42.000 --> 00:24:48.000
We're going to drop it. It could be the greatest system.

269
00:24:48.000 --> 00:24:57.000
But if you put it in the hands of one who doesn't know, doesn't have the capability to bear it, it will still leave us lacking.

270
00:24:57.000 --> 00:25:03.000
Brandon talked last week about blessed is the man who meditates on the law of the Lord in Psalm 1.

271
00:25:03.000 --> 00:25:15.000
The law is good. The law tells us how to live. But we in and of ourselves find ourselves falling short and not just falling short a little bit, right?

272
00:25:15.000 --> 00:25:24.000
Go through the 10 commandments. We've broken all of them. Jesus says if you even have a desire in your mind to anger towards your brother,

273
00:25:24.000 --> 00:25:32.000
you've already committed murder. Like, he doesn't want us to just be able to follow a prescription. He wants us to be transformed to come alive.

274
00:25:32.000 --> 00:25:37.000
So we don't need a how. We need a who.

275
00:25:37.000 --> 00:25:52.000
So this is where we're going to drop down a little bit. Because I want us to not just go out with a good feeling about how great everything is going to be and how crazy it is now.

276
00:25:52.000 --> 00:26:03.000
I want us to leave here recognizing that this and all of Scripture comes down all the way to the ground level. All the way down.

277
00:26:03.000 --> 00:26:14.000
It's very concrete. Despite maybe our temptation. So I mean, we've discussed cosmic conflict, the creator's character and the true King.

278
00:26:14.000 --> 00:26:29.000
But I want it to be with us at all times. So in the last remaining time that we have, I'm going to drop down like I said and try to hit things that I need to hear.

279
00:26:29.000 --> 00:26:38.000
And then I hope that some of you find helpful as well. So going back, we do to point to the answer to our first question, what kind of story are we in right now?

280
00:26:38.000 --> 00:26:47.000
So we do live and we talked about this a little bit in an age of intense conflict, right? Political comes to mind.

281
00:26:47.000 --> 00:26:55.000
There are wars that are like hot wars for the first time, maybe in a lot of regions in my lifetime.

282
00:26:56.000 --> 00:27:03.000
Some of you can remember other times, but because of our access to information, it's very much in our face.

283
00:27:03.000 --> 00:27:10.000
Even though we quickly forget, right? It's a wild thing. There's politics, there's foreign wars. You don't even have to go that deep.

284
00:27:10.000 --> 00:27:19.000
You can just log on to Facebook or Instagram and see all kinds of arguments about what's fake news and which side had this right.

285
00:27:19.000 --> 00:27:25.000
And what happened here and how terrible are they, them over there?

286
00:27:25.000 --> 00:27:43.000
I was talking to a good friend of mine, not that long ago. And he like me has a young son and he said to me, he said, you know, I'm really grateful for the time we live in because I really don't want my son,

287
00:27:43.000 --> 00:27:51.000
I don't want your sons to have to go to war ever. I would hate for them to be conscripted into the service.

288
00:27:51.000 --> 00:28:09.000
And I was like, I don't want that either. But while I appreciate that, I think I kind of was thinking while I was going through this, I was like, well, actually the reality is my sons, my daughter, me, each of us here,

289
00:28:09.000 --> 00:28:19.000
we were born into a time of war. We dress things up and try to feel like we live in peacetime.

290
00:28:19.000 --> 00:28:35.000
But the fact is, we've been born into a conflict that was raging before us, that's continuing on, and the stakes are actually a lot higher than the geopolitical conflicts that we read about in the news, right?

291
00:28:35.000 --> 00:28:48.000
These are souls, this is eternity. This isn't, oh, they gained some ground for a century. This is forever. And these are souls.

292
00:28:48.000 --> 00:29:01.000
See, it's Lewis at one point, I'm going to give him two because I'm a Lewis guy, at one point says, you know, nations fall, kingdoms fall, but the people that you interact with every day, they're made for eternity.

293
00:29:01.000 --> 00:29:11.000
The institutions that we build here will, outside of the church, will fall, right? You can look all across human history, empires fall.

294
00:29:11.000 --> 00:29:29.000
But one name, one kingdom, one institution, family of God, lasts forever. So, you may never pick up a physical weapon. I hope that my children never have to be forced into the military if they make that choice. That's a different story.

295
00:29:29.000 --> 00:29:48.000
We'll pray for that, but regardless of whether you ever pick up a physical weapon, experience physical violence, ever face a firing squad or physical torment, make no mistake, you are under fire.

296
00:29:48.000 --> 00:30:04.000
The moment that you became a believer, if you have made that declaration, you have positioned yourself as an enemy to what is called the Lord of this current age, Satan.

297
00:30:04.000 --> 00:30:16.000
And one writer put it this way, when you became a Christian, you established a new relationship with the powers of darkness. I mean, you got a target.

298
00:30:16.000 --> 00:30:28.000
Now, David Platt actually recently, I just saw a quote from him that I couldn't not throw in. You're in a wrestling match with cosmic powers of darkness. Whether you realize it or not, that's kind of sobering.

299
00:30:28.000 --> 00:30:40.000
Most of us think we live in peacetime, right? I get my quiet time. I go to church on Sunday. I don't cheat on my taxes. I don't cheat on my spouse. I do a decent job at work.

300
00:30:40.000 --> 00:30:51.000
Things are going to work out. But Jesus doesn't actually hide this reality at all. He says, if anyone would come after me, he must deny himself. Take up his cross and follow me.

301
00:30:51.000 --> 00:31:04.000
That's not super exciting for a peacetime. And then in John 1633, in the world you will have tribulation. You may have tribulation. It might be tough some days.

302
00:31:04.000 --> 00:31:10.000
You will have tribulation, but take heart. I have overcome the world.

303
00:31:10.000 --> 00:31:18.000
So, oh man, time is getting tight.

304
00:31:18.000 --> 00:31:35.000
Alright, so we talked earlier about false kings, fabricated kingdoms, disordered fears. So, just quick note on that.

305
00:31:35.000 --> 00:31:47.000
There are many great folks out there creating great content. Christians, some non-Christians that are common grace putting stuff out there that's really helpful.

306
00:31:47.000 --> 00:32:02.000
I don't think that that's something that we have to trash. But I think we have to be careful about how we approach them, how we submit to the rulers of this world, the kings, so to speak, of our age.

307
00:32:03.000 --> 00:32:12.000
I saw the other day and I've heard from a few folks that Joe Rogan is going to church. People were very excited about this.

308
00:32:12.000 --> 00:32:21.000
Because he's someone who is obviously not a believer and he's attending church. And I got a text message that said, we need to pray.

309
00:32:21.000 --> 00:32:41.000
And I said, that's great. We do. We should pray for all the lost. But regardless of what happens with that king, that ruler, that person with influence, and this could go for anyone that you may be value their input from a non-Christian standpoint.

310
00:32:42.000 --> 00:32:48.000
Wouldn't you be careful not to be more invested in that than the words that we get from our true king?

311
00:32:48.000 --> 00:33:07.000
And then the last point I think is examining ourselves. Have we in a world with unimaginable, even a century ago, unimaginable resources and comforts and authority, the things that we can do, have we set ourselves up as false kings?

312
00:33:07.000 --> 00:33:20.000
Do we fabricate kingdoms and do we allow disordered fears to speak and have the loudest voice in the decisions that we make?

313
00:33:24.000 --> 00:33:26.000
Kiss the sun.

314
00:33:27.000 --> 00:33:45.000
I think that this is something that we would all do well to meditate on. The sun is the one who brings justice. He's also the one who brings mercy.

315
00:33:45.000 --> 00:33:52.000
We see in our opening passage of scripture this morning, Isaiah 42, I'm going to read that again.

316
00:34:16.000 --> 00:34:30.000
Maybe today you are hungry for justice. Maybe you see the wrong in the world. Wrong has been committed against you. Maybe wrong against the unborn.

317
00:34:30.000 --> 00:34:43.000
Maybe against children in abusive homes. Maybe people in war zones. Take heart. He's bringing justice.

318
00:34:44.000 --> 00:34:54.000
Maybe today you desperately long for mercy. Maybe you are very aware of your brokenness or the brokenness of someone near you.

319
00:34:55.000 --> 00:35:05.000
Take heart. His mercy is more than enough. A bruised reed, he went out and broke.

320
00:35:09.000 --> 00:35:18.000
Jesus says in Matthew 11, and this is the king. This is the one who will bear the rod of iron. This is him. This is who's talking.

321
00:35:18.000 --> 00:35:28.000
Come to me. All who labor and are heavy laden, and I will give you rest. Take my yoke up on you and learn from me, for I am gentle and lowly in heart.

322
00:35:29.000 --> 00:35:35.000
And you will find rest for your souls. Let's get real practical here at the end.

323
00:35:35.000 --> 00:35:42.000
My brother is here today. I'm grateful to have a little bit of time with him.

324
00:35:43.000 --> 00:35:53.000
The last few years he's gotten really into jiu-jitsu. Some of you may not be familiar, but it's martial art. It's kind of like wrestling. I guess some people might think.

325
00:35:54.000 --> 00:36:03.000
But it's designed specifically for a smaller, weaker individual to be able to defend themselves against a larger, stronger individual.

326
00:36:03.000 --> 00:36:15.000
In fact, it's really counterintuitive. When it was first introduced to the masses it seemed wild, because it actually puts you on your back with your opponent on top of you, which has got to be the most vulnerable position.

327
00:36:16.000 --> 00:36:26.000
Anybody who's ever seen a schoolyard fight knows that is not where you want to be. Flat on your back, on the ground with somebody raining down on you.

328
00:36:26.000 --> 00:36:38.000
My wife broke up one of these just the other day at school. But in fact, jiu-jitsu is designed for this. And they call that position the most vulnerable position, the guard. It's your guard.

329
00:36:39.000 --> 00:36:47.000
Wow. But over time, the decades since that's been introduced to the masses, it's become apparent. This is actually really effective.

330
00:36:47.000 --> 00:37:05.000
So what seemed to be the most vulnerable position has actually become a position of strength. That's not unlike what we're told to do. Put yourself in a vulnerable position. The thing that the world says you could never do and succeed.

331
00:37:05.000 --> 00:37:23.000
Love your enemy. Turn the other cheek. Choose to serve rather than being served. Take up your cross. That's nuts. That's crazy. Lay down flat on your back. Let your opponent get on top of you. You're bigger, stronger opponent.

332
00:37:23.000 --> 00:37:46.000
But that is how this upside-down kingdom, as you may have heard it called, works with this king. Because he is just. He does bear the rod of iron. But he is also merciful. And he will embrace those who embrace him.

333
00:37:46.000 --> 00:38:09.000
In fact, we are told that those who take refuge in him will be blessed. So I know I'm running out of time. So I just want to lay this out as a challenge and a word of hope to each of us.

334
00:38:10.000 --> 00:38:35.000
Men who are here, some of you are husbands, many fathers, grandfathers, I know even, in the room. As you think about your role, put on the armor of God. And remember in Ephesians when he talks about this armor.

335
00:38:35.000 --> 00:38:53.000
And then when Jesus tells Peter that the gates of hell will not prevail, I think I want you to keep in mind that gates are not an offensive weapon. We are meant to engage with the evil one. We don't hunker down and put our walls up.

336
00:38:53.000 --> 00:39:12.000
There's a sword, and it's the word. So men, take heart. Cover your family with prayer. As we go through the Psalms of the summer, engage with that. Lament where we lament. Praise where we can praise. Know that he can handle both.

337
00:39:13.000 --> 00:39:30.000
Women, some of you are wives, some mothers, many friends, different stages of life. But the Proverbs 31 woman gets thrown around a lot. And I've seen that burden crush women the way that it's presented.

338
00:39:30.000 --> 00:39:52.000
So when you hear the verse 25 in Proverbs 31, strength and dignity are her clothing, and she laughs at the time to come. Christ is that strength and dignity. And you can laugh because you know that he holds it and he's coming back.

339
00:39:53.000 --> 00:40:13.000
And so our last question, how does it end? Well, kiss the sun. Lest he be angry and you perish in the way, for his wrath is quickly kindled. But blessed are all who take refuge in him. Christ our King, he's come. He's risen.

340
00:40:14.000 --> 00:40:33.000
He's defeated our enemy, but the battle rages until he returns. So let's seek hope in him. And as we come to the table this morning, Brandon's going to mention that. I just hope that you're blessed by the truth of a just and merciful King, Jesus. Let's pray.

341
00:40:34.000 --> 00:40:57.000
Father, we thank you. Thank you for our King. I pray that the words that you've poured out through your scriptures would sink deep into our hearts and changes, that they would not just be good ideas, but that they would be truth that transforms and upholds us in our weakness and our brokenness.

342
00:40:58.000 --> 00:41:20.000
I pray blessing on each who are here, blessing on your church around the globe, Lord, as we seek to wage this paradoxical war against the evil one and the brokenness in our own hearts. Thank you for your spirit that does the work for us and intercedes for us even now, Lord.

343
00:41:20.000 --> 00:41:24.000
Pray this in the name of our King. Amen.

